\section*{Overview}
This document summarizes \textbf{testable predictions} of the \textbf{Hamiltonian Crystal framework}, including experimental and high-energy physics contexts. Observables are categorized as:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Actionable Today:} Measurable with current experimental setups.  
    \item \textbf{For Future Research:} Requires advanced instrumentation, high-energy systems, or exotic quantum simulators.
\end{itemize}

The system is defined by the Hamiltonian
\[
H = \sum_{p \in \mathbb{P}} \omega_p N_p, \quad \omega_p = \log p, \quad N_p = a_p^\dagger a_p,
\]
with \textbf{prime orbit lengths}:
\[
L_{p,n} = n \log p, \quad n \in \mathbb{Z}^+.
\]

